<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/71183337-john"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/71183337-john">John</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It was a good idea to make a separate reviewing page for the English reviews. The bulk of the reviews were written in Dutch with only a few hundred in<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It was a good idea to make a separate reviewing page for the English reviews. The bulk of the reviews were written in Dutch with only a few hundred in English, which makes it seem like a relatively-unknown title. New readers might be deterred by this. Perhaps someone from your PR team could collect more english reviews.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
